==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Phosphoresce
<hw>Phos`phor*esce"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Phosphoresced</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Phosphorescing</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To shine as phosphorus; to be
phosphorescent; to emit a phosphoric light. Generally, to emit light at
temperatures too low to excite incandescent radiation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To emit light after a source of illumination has
been removed; to exhibit phosphorescence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phosphorescence</ent>⟦br⟧
